{"id":40718,"date":"2023-07-07T02:16:38","date_gmt":"2023-07-06T22:16:38","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/?p=40718"},"modified":"2023-09-04T13:19:17","modified_gmt":"2023-09-04T09:19:17","slug":"exaggerated-recitation","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2023\/07\/07\/exaggerated-recitation\/","title":{"rendered":"Hadith on Recitation: Warning not to exaggerate with the Quran"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Mihjan ibn al-Adra\u2019 reported: I was eager to meet the Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, one night, and he came out to fulfill one of his needs. The Prophet saw me, took my hand, and we set out. We passed by a man who was praying loudly with the Quran. The Prophet said, \u201c<strong>Perhaps he is being ostentatious.<\/strong>\u201d I said, \u201cO Messenger of Allah, you recite the Quran aloud.\u201d The Prophet raised his hands, then he said, \u201c<strong>Verily, you will never achieve this matter by exaggeration<\/strong>.\u201d Then, he came out another night, and we passed by a man praying with the Quran. I said, \u201cPerhaps he is being ostentatious.\u201d The Prophet said, \u201c<strong>Nay, rather he is penitent<\/strong>.\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Source: Musnad Ah\u0323mad 18971<\/p>\n<p>Grade: <em>Hasan<\/em> (fair) according to Al-Albani<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">\u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0645\u0650\u062d\u0652\u062c\u064e\u0646\u0650 \u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u0627\u0644\u0652\u0623\u064e\u062f\u0652\u0631\u064e\u0639\u0650 \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0643\u064f\u0646\u0652\u062a\u064f \u0623\u064e\u062d\u0652\u0631\u064f\u0633\u064f \u0627\u0644\u0646\u064e\u0651\u0628\u0650\u064a\u064e\u0651 \u0635\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0647\u0650 \u0648\u064e\u0633\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0645\u064e \u0630\u064e\u0627\u062a\u064e \u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0644\u064e\u0629\u06